[1
Date: Wed 5 Dec 2001
From: Dale E. Reddick <dereddick@islc.net>


Four More Human Cases of West Nile Virus Infection in Georgia
-------------------------------------------------------------
Georgia Public Radio this morning is reporting that 4 more human cases of
West Nile virus infection have been found in the state. The cases occurred
during September and October, but laboratory confirmation did come about
until the present because of testing delays. Those delays were due to the
anthrax threat and the large number of laboratory tests undertaken to detect
anthrax.

These 4 cases bring the total number of human WNV cases in Georgia to 5. Of
theses 4 men infected, one man from Pierce County (Southeast Georgia)
remains hospitalized for encephalitis. The 3 other individuals have
recovered. They are from Richmond (Augusta), Wayne, and Macon Counties.

--
Dale E. Reddick
<dereddick@islc.net>

